Hello. This is probably a silly question, but I can't figure out how to make the game wait before doing the action I have coded it to do (load the last quicksave). I currently have this code segment:

 public override void OnActive()

 {

 UnityEngine.Debug.Log("[FK] Time Traveling");

 Game \_game = GamePersistence.LoadGame("quicksave", HighLogic.SaveFolder, true, true);

//Wait 3 Seconds here

 \_game.Start();

}

If someone could please help me out here and possible direct me to a good source to look off of that would be great. ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif) Thanks

> 
> public void OnActive(){    StartCoroutine(CoroutineExample());}public System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable CoroutineExample(){    yield return new WaitForSeconds(3);    game.Start();}
> 
> 
> 
> 
> Look up unity coroutines for more info

